#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn56.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.30:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga "
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Gavampatisutta "
msgstr "30. With Gavampati "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: cetesu → cetīsu (bj) | cetiyesu (s1-3)
#. VAR: sahañcanike → sahajātiyaṃ (bj) | sahajaniye (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn56.30:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā therā bhikkhū cetesu viharanti sahañcanike. "
msgstr "At one time several mendicants were staying in the land of the Cetis at Sahajāti. "

msgctxt "sn56.30:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulānaṃ therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṃ maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi: "
msgstr "Now at that time, after the meal, on return from alms-round, several senior mendicants sat together in the pavilion and this discussion came up among them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.30:1.3"
msgid "“yo nu kho, āvuso, dukkhaṃ passati dukkhasamudayampi so passati, dukkhanirodhampi passati, dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadampi passatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, does someone who sees suffering also see the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering?” "

# NOTE: read there
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.437, sc2
#. VAR: gavampati thero → gavampatitthero (s1-3, km) | gavampati there (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.30:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā gavampati thero bhikkhū etadavoca: "
msgstr "When they said this, Venerable Gavampati said to those senior mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.30:2.2"
msgid "“sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "“Reverends, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn56.30:2.3"
msgid "‘yo, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ passati dukkhasamudayampi so passati, dukkhanirodhampi passati, dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadampi passati. "
msgstr "‘Someone who sees suffering also sees the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn56.30:2.4"
msgid "Yo dukkhasamudayaṃ passati dukkhampi so passati, dukkhanirodhampi passati, dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadampi passati. "
msgstr "Someone who sees the origin of suffering also sees suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn56.30:2.5"
msgid "Yo dukkhanirodhaṃ passati dukkhampi so passati, dukkhasamudayampi passati, dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadampi passati. "
msgstr "Someone who sees the cessation of suffering also sees suffering, the origin of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn56.30:2.6"
msgid "Yo dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ passati dukkhampi so passati, dukkhasamudayampi passati, dukkhanirodhampi passatī’”ti. "
msgstr "Someone who sees the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering also sees suffering, the origin of suffering, and the cessation of suffering.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.30:2.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.30:2.8"
msgid "Koṭigāmavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.30:3.1"
msgid "Dve vajjī sammāsambuddho, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.30:3.2"
msgid "arahaṃ āsavakkhayo; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.30:3.3"
msgid "Mittaṃ tathā ca loko ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn56.30:3.4"
msgid "pariññeyyaṃ gavampatīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
